Durban - A man is due to appear in the Verulam Magistrate's Court on Monday, in connection with a body that was found floating in a dam near Cornubia, on Friday. According to KwaZulu Natal police spokesman, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, the body was discovered by young boys who were cutting sugar cane near the dam at around 10:30 am. Mbele said police were notified and the victim's body was retrieved from the dam by SAPS search and rescue the same day. "The deceased who was wearing a pair of blue jeans, and a white and navy T-shirt sustained stab wounds and appeared to have been assaulted." A case of murder was opened. Mbele said the motive for the attack was unknown. "Verulam detectives worked around the clock to solve the murder case which led to the arrest of the suspect." She said the victim who is his 20s, had not been identified. DAILY NEWS   